pc:TextEquiv.pc:Unicode: " Weeping may endure for a night, but joy cometh in the morning." Psalm 30 : 5.
1. Oh, wea- - ry pil-grim, lift your head, For joy cometh in the morning!
2. Ye fee-ble - saints, dismiss your fears, For joy cometh in the morning!
3. Let ev - 'ry tear - ful eye be dry, For joy cometh in the morning!
4. Our God will wipe our tears a - way, For joy cometh in the morning
For God in his own word has said That joy cometh in the morning.
And weeping mourners, dry your tears, For joy cometh in the morning.
And ev - 'ry trembling sin-ner hope, For joy cometh in the morning.
Sor - row and sigh-ing flee a - way, For joy cometh in the morning.
Joy cometh in the morning ! Joy cometh in the morning ! Weeping may en-
dure, may en-dure for a night, But joy cometh in the morning.
